  <insight>
    <p>Enumerated values are a great use case for <pf>switch</pf> statements. We have a finite list of
      items that all have unique integer values. We could write <pf>suitToString</pf> with if/else logic, but
      the switch is a little more succinct.</p>
  </insight>

  <exercise label="structs_enum-values-ex-1"
            xml:id="structs_enum-values-ex-1"
            adaptive="yes"
            indentation="hide">
    <statement>
      <p>Construct a <pf>Standing</pf> enum with values for FRESHMAN, SOPHOMORE, JUNIOR, and SENIOR such
        that they have the values 9, 10, 11, and 12.</p>
    </statement>
    <blocks>
      <block>
        <choice correct="yes">
          <cline>enum class Standing {</cline>
        </choice>
        <choice>
          <cline>struct Standing {</cline>
        </choice>
        <choice>
          <cline>enum Standing {</cline>
        </choice>
      </block>
      <block>
        <choice correct="yes">
          <cline>  FRESHMAN = 9,</cline>
        </choice>
        <choice>
          <cline>  FRESHMAN,</cline>
        </choice>
      </block>
      <block>
        <cline>  SOPHOMORE,</cline>
      </block>
      <block>
        <cline>  JUNIOR,</cline>
      </block>
      <block>
        <cline>  SENIOR</cline>
        <cline>};</cline>
      </block>
    </blocks>
  </exercise>


